                                   simple.vim

Set of minimal syntax file for Vim, inspired by [nothings]' highlighting and by
[simpc-mode] (now [nothings-mode]).  Its goal is to offer minimal visual
distraction when editings ource code, while leaving you with an option to use
any colour theme your want.

[nothings]: https://github.com/nothings
[simpc-mode]: https://github.com/rexim/simpc-mode
[nothings-mode]: https://github.com/rexim/simpc-mode


                                 Installation

Copy `.vim` files to somewhere in your `runtimepath`, i.e. to `~/.config/nvim
/syntax/`. That's all.


